NOW  THIS  DEED  WITNESSES:
1. The Customer hereby  assigns  to the  Lender as beneficial  owner all of its  right title  and  interest in the Goods  as  security for the   repayment  of the   of the Loan and the payment of interest in  the  manner  and   at  the times  specified in Part III of the Schedule to the Loan Application.
2. The  Customer agrees  with  the Lender :
(a.) to  make  the  payments required by  Part III  of the  Schedule to the Loan Application  to the  office  of the  Lender set out below. Any  payments  remitted  by  past shall be at the Customer’s  risk  until  received  by the Lender.   No  cheque  shall  be deemed  to be  a   payment  until  cleared ;
(b.) to  keep  the  goods  in good  order  and  repair  by  not  to  create  any  lien  in respect  thereof;
(c.) to insure  the Goods  for  their  full insurable   value and  to  keep  them  so insured  during  the term of this  Mortgage against  fire  accident  and  theft and to pay all premiums in respect  thereof and  to  produce  to  the  lender  evidence of  such payment on or before  the  renewal date of  such  policy; 
(d.) that   the  Lender   shall be  entitled  to receive  and/or  appropriate  any  insurance  monies  becoming due in respect of the loss of or  damaged to the Goods  and  the Customer  hereby  appoints  the Lender  and all of its officers  severally as its    Attorney  to  recover   and/or  comprise  any  claim  of loss or damaged  under any  such  insurance  policy  and to give  valid and effectual  receipts  and  discharges  in  respect  thereof ;
(e.) to  notify  the  Lender  immediately  of  any  damage  to the goods;
(f.) not  without  the  approval of the  Lender to move the  Goods  from  their  present  location;
(g.) to produce the goods  for   inspection by the  Lender as   required;
(h.) that  the Customer  will  not   without  the  prior  written  consent  of the  Lender  sell  dispose  of  or  encumber  the  Goods  or  any  right  title  or  interest  therein  nor  attempt  or  agree  to do so;
(i.) to  notify  the  Lender  of  any  change  of address  of the  Customer;
(j.) to  repay   to the  Lender  on demand  any  monies  which  it   may see  fit  to pay  to make   good  any  failure  by the  Customer  to  comply  with  any of the  Customer’s  obligations  hereunder  and  any  other  expense  that  may be  incurred  in  consequence  or  arising  out  of  default  by the   Customer;
(k. that  the  Lender   is  hereby   irrevocably   authorized  to enter  any  premises  where  it  believes  the Goods   may  be located  for the purpose of inspecting  or  testing  them or  taking   possession   thereof  pursuant  to  the  powers    contained  or  implied  herein;
(l.) that  the  Lender  is  hereby  irrevocably  authorized  to use  the name  and act on behalf  of the  Customer  in  exercising  any  rights  or  instituting  or  carrying  on or  enforcing  any legal  proceedings  which  it  thinks  desirable  to  protect  its  rights  in the  Goods.
(m.) that  a   certificate  purporting  to be   signed   by the   manager,  assistant   manager,  credit manager or other  officer   of the  Lender   as   to  the  amount  owing  the   Customer to the Lender  shall  in  the  absence  of  fraud  be  prima  facie  evidence  of the  facts  stated  therein;
(n.) to pay  or  cause  to be paid  as  they  become   due  and  payable  all taxes,  assessments   and governmental   charges   lawfully  levied  or  assessed  or  imposed  upon the goods.
3. It  is   hereby   agreed   and  declared  as  follows;
(a.) that  if the  Customer   has  made  a  false  statement  in connection  with its  application for the  loan  referred  to above,  or if
(b.) the Customer  makes  default  in payment  of any  principal  or  interest  payable  in respect of the   said  loan; or
(c.) the Customer   commits  any   breach   of the  provisions  of  this   mortgage  of
(d.) any  cheque  given by  the  Customer  to the  supplier  as  or  as   part   of the  deposit  on the  sale  of the Goods  to it is dishonored  or any  goods  traded  in by the Customer  to the  supplier  in connection  with  such  sale  or  not  its  absolute  unencumbered  property; or 
(e.) execution or  distress  is  issued   against  the  Customer or its  Goods  or  a  petition  or  resolution  for  its  winding up is  presented  or proposed; or
(f.) any   event  occurs  constituting  an act  or  bankruptcy on the part  of the Customer  then  and in  any   such  case  the  Lender  may  exercise  the  power  conferred  by  Clause  4  hereof.
4. Upon  the  happening   of  any  of the  events  referred  to  in  Clause  5  the  Lender  shall be  entitled  (in  addition to  exercising   any powers  implied  by law  in favor  of  mortgagees  of  goods) :  -
(a.) to   seize  and take  possession of the goods  or  any  part  thereof  without  prior  notice  to the  Customer.
(b.) either  with  or without  seizing  the goods  and  without  notice  to the  Customer  sell or  dispose of  the  Goods  or any  part  thereof  either  at  auction  or  by private   treaty  ( including  disposal  to or through  traders  dealing  in goods  of  a like  description)   and  either  in one  lot  or  several  lots  at one or different  times  and  either  for  cash  or  on  terms (including  lease  hire  purchase  mortgage  back  or  otherwise) ,  and  subject  to such other  conditions   as  the  Lender  may  think fit;
(c.) give   valid  discharges  for  purchase   monies  or other   consideration  payable  in respect of the   disposal of the  Goods.  No such  sale or  disposal  shall  be  set  aside on the  grounds  that  it  was  not  properly  authorized  or  that any  requisite  notice was  not duly  given.  No  purchaser  shall be concerned  to see  or  enquire  whether  such  sake  have been  properly  authorized  or  that  the  Lender’s  power  have been  properly  and  regularly  exercised;
(d.) execute   any  transfer  assignment  or  other  instrument  which the  Lender   may  consider  necessary  to give  effect  to any  such  sale or disposal.  All  monies   received  on such  sale  shall  be  applied  firstly  in payment  of all  costs  charges  and  expenses properly  incurred  by the Lender  of  any  incidental  to  the sale or disposal   or  any  attempted  sale  or disposal  
( including   expenses  of  storage  of the  Goods  while  awaiting disposal)  and  secondly  in payment of interest at the  rate  provided  in  the Application  and  thirdly  in  reduction  of the  principal  sum  and  other  monies  secured  by  or  payable  hereunder  as  provide in the  Application and the  residue (if any)  shall be  paid  to the  person  beneficially  entitled  to  the  Goods  or  authorized   to give  receipts  for  the  proceeds  of  the  thereof;
5. After   exercising  the powers of seizing  the Goods  the  Lender  may in  its  discretion   permit   the  Customer   to resume  the  possession  thereof  and in  that  event  the  Customer  shall  hold  the  goods   subject  to the provisions  of this  mortgage  as if seizure  had  not taken  place  and  except  in so far as  the Lender  may expressly  specify  in writing the Lender  shall   not be   permitting  the Customer  to resume  possession  deemed  to have  waived  any default or other  event  as if  referred  to in Clause 3.
6. Upon  payment  by the Lender  of  all monies  secured  hereby  or  payable  hereunder  the lender  shall at  the  Customer’s  expense  execute  such  reassignment  of the  Goods  or  such   discharge of this  Mortgage as  the  Customer may  reasonably  require  provided  however   that  the Lender  shall not be  bound to accept  payment  otherwise  than by the installments  referred  to in the  application.
7. Where  there   are  two  or more  Customers  they  shall  be bound  hereunder  jointly  and  severally;  the Lender’s  rights   and powers  may be  exercised  by its  nominees  or  assigns.
8. For  the  consideration  aforesaid  the  Customer hereby   irrevocably  appoints  the manager   and  all other  officers  of the  Lender  authorized  by it in that behalf jointly  and  severally  as  the   Customer’s  Attorney  for the doing  of  all acts  including  the  execution  of  documents  and  the  taking  of legal  proceedings  which Lender  shall  in its  absolute  discretion  require  for the perfecting of its  title  to the  Goods  for  further  assuring  them  to it  or for  gaining  possession  thereof  or for  or  in  connection  with   the   enforcement  of  any  of  the Lender’s   rights  or  powers   hereunder.
9. The  powers  contained  on  Part III  of  Schedule  4  to the  instruments  Act  ( Chapter 254)  shall be  deemed  to be in  addition  to the powers  conferred  by its  Mortgage   to the  extent  (if any)   that   the   implied  covenants  and  agreements  contained  in  Parts  I  and II  of  Schedule  4  of  the said  Act conflict  with the provisions of  this  agreement  such  implied  covenants  and  agreement  are   hereby  varied  or  excluded (as  the  case  may be) to the  intent  of  such  inconsistency.
10. In this  Agreement  the  Lender  means Courts(PNG)  Limited  whose  address  for payment is Lot  15  Sec  62  Spring   Garden  Road  Hohola  and whose  postal   address  is P.O. Box  1233, BOROKO.
11. This  Mortgage is  entered  into under  and is to be  construed in accordance  with  the Laws of Papua New  Guinea.
12. Documentation  Fee  of K120.00   is non- refundable  upon  cancellation.

IN  WITNESS  WHEREOF THIS    Mortgage  has  been  signed  by the  Customer  to take  effect  on the  date first  herein  before  written.
